# Sprint 9 deploy — what Docker should never ship into a build context.
# Keep this list narrow: every entry is something that either:
#   - bloats the build context (node_modules, .next),
#   - leaks secrets (.env*),
#   - or breaks build caching by changing on every run (.turbo, coverage).

# Dependencies — Dockerfile reinstalls from the lockfile.
node_modules
**/node_modules

# Build outputs — Dockerfile builds fresh.
.next
**/.next
dist
**/dist
build
**/build
.turbo
**/.turbo
coverage
**/coverage

# Tooling state that shouldn't ride along.
.git
.github
.vscode
.idea
.DS_Store
*.log
logs
pgdata
redisdata

# Anything that looks like a local upload / runtime storage volume.
# Anchored to the build-context root so we don't also strip source dirs
# (apps/api/src/storage/ + apps/api/src/uploads/ exist).
/storage
/uploads
apps/api/uploads
apps/api/storage

# Secrets — must never enter an image.
.env
.env.*
!.env.example

# Repo docs / dev tooling — not needed in any runtime image.
README.md
docs/
.gitignore
.gitattributes
.editorconfig
.prettierrc
.prettierignore
docker-compose.yml
deploy/

# IDE / OS noise
Thumbs.db
*.swp
